  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 01:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] V5A smart-entry filter still clears weekday edge, weekend stays blocked\n\n**Task:** Audit the current PM smart-entry parameters using the fresh `v5a-shadow-validation.jsonl` set, with outcomes inferred from the next 5-minute BTC print and the live bot's contrarian YES-only rule.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- Parsed **1,225** V5A shadow rows and **1,170** contiguous 5-minute outcome pairs.\n- Raw V5A improved over legacy v4.1: **61.8% WR / +$13.50 avg contrarian BTC move** vs v4.1 **58.0% / +$10.53**.\n- V5A's lower-bound block is doing useful work: legacy passes blocked by V5A were only **48.6% WR / +$3.16**.\n- Current live-core projection (`bias<0`, `45<=abs_bias<=70`, active hours `11/12/20`) produced **106 samples, 60.4% WR, +$13.83 avg contrarian BTC move**.\n- Dropping 20 UTC is not justified yet: hours `11/12` only were **60.8% WR / +$11.16**, while 20 UTC alone was **59.3% WR / +$21.63**.\n- May 2 Saturday subset stayed weak despite nominal hit rate: V5A **55.6% WR but -$7.72 avg move**, and V5A-blocked legacy passes were **0/2**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p2-v5a-smart-entry-audit-2026-05-03-0104.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** The core weekday filter is still viable: reliability is above 60% and the edge proxy is positive after applying the actual live constraints. But the weekend evidence is not good enough to loosen anything. The Saturday subset confirms why the weekend filter exists: the hit rate can look acceptable while directional payoff quality is negative.\n\n**Decision:** No live config change. Keep **weekend filter ON**, **YES-only**, `active_hours=[11,12,20]`, `bias_threshold=45`, and `max_bias=70`. Keep 20 UTC on probation, not removed.\n\n**Next:** On the next P2 pass, test whether 20 UTC should require an additional copy/regime confirmation rather than being cut outright.\n\n## 2026-05-03 01:04 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Weak fair-price noise increased after midnight\n\n**Task:** Compare pre-midnight vs post-midnight PM shadow reject mixes under the current `mixed_transition / expanding / sentiment_impulse_up` alpha context, while waiting for the first settled alpha-tagged outcome rows.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- Parsed PM signal rows from `2026-05-02 22:46 UTC` onward.\n- **Pre-midnight sample:** 67 rows: strong-bias **34**, live price-band **16**, weak-bias live-band **9**, price-low **45**, price-high **6**.\n- **Post-midnight sample:** 65 rows: strong-bias **27**, live price-band **21**, weak-bias live-band **17**, price-low **41**, price-high **3**.\n- Reject mix shifted from more strong-but-sub-50 ambiguity to more weak-bias fair-price noise.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p2-pre-vs-post-midnight-shadow-mix-2026-05-03-0104.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** Price alone ",
